Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with graham crackers. Sprinkle evenly with pecans. In a small saucepan over medium heat, combine sugar, butter and margarine. Bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes. Remove from heat and spoon mixture over pecans, coating well. Bake in preheated oven 12 minutes, until golden. Cool completely before serving.